# Prediction League — Project Rules

## Do not break

- **Match logic** — match definitions, match rendering, match card display, archive behavior
- **XP logic** — `computeXpBreakdown`, `settleLivePredictionIfNeeded`, XP accumulation, profile XP
- **Live polling** — `runTrackedLivePoll`, `getLiveTrackedMatches`, `applyLiveGameToCards`, server proxy
- **Wallet behavior** — wallet connect/disconnect, Base chain switching, wagmi/viem integration
- **Navigation** — all `show*View()` functions must remove `.active` from every other view
- **Prediction flow** — form locking after kickoff, prediction saving to localStorage, deadline logic
- **i18n** — both EN and RU translations must stay in sync, use `T()` for all user-facing text
- **localStorage keys** — never rename storage keys without a migration path

## Code style

- Vanilla JS — no frameworks, no TypeScript
- Mobile-first CSS — test on narrow screens first
- Dark premium theme — no bright backgrounds, no neon overload
- Incremental changes only — no rewrites, no "let me refactor this whole file"

## Architecture

- `script.js` — all frontend logic (single file, no module splitting for now)
- `server.mjs` — Node.js backend: static files + API-Football proxy with caching
- `web3/` — wallet modules, compiled into `wallet.bundle.js` via esbuild
- `tracked-matches.json` — server-side match config (read by `server.mjs` on each request)

## When adding matches

1. Add new match objects to the `matches` array in `script.js`
2. Mark old matches with `archived: true` (keep them for My Bets archive)
3. Update `tracked-matches.json` with the same match IDs and API hints
4. Sort active matches by `kickoffMs` ascending (earlier matches first)
5. Use unique IDs that don't conflict with existing match IDs

## When editing server.mjs

- Keep API call count low — respect the 100 requests/day free tier
- Use caching (`fixturesCache`, `eventsCache`, `negEmptyUntil`) before making upstream calls
- `normalizeFixture` must return a consistent shape for all matches
- `enrichWithEvents` fetches goal scorer data — cache aggressively for final matches
